Pseudo-classes- :pseudo-class
Pseudo-element- ::pseudo-element 
NOTE: ::first-line/::first-letter pseudo-elements can only be applied to block-level elements.
The ::before and ::after Pseudo-elements can be used to add content before and after an element, like an h1 or p element.





/* Need help creating backgrounds using url images */
/* Here is the code for url images just so I can practice */
body {
	background-image: url()
	background-repeat: no-repeat;
	background-repeat: repeat-x; repeat-y;
	background-position: right top;
}
/* alt. code for background is {
	background: #ffffff url() no-repeat right top;
	margin-right:200px
}



x is the horizontal axis
y is the vertical axis
no-repeat keeps the image from repeating across the page
background-position can be set based on top and bottom/ left and right
background-attachment sets whether the background is fixed or scrolls with the rest of the page
When using the shorthand property the order of the property values is:

background-color
background-image
background-repeat
background-attachment
background-position

/* CSS Box Model */
(SMALLEST BOX)Content - The content of the box, where text and images appear
(BIGGER BOX)Padding - Clears an area around the content. The padding is transparent
(SLIGHTLY BIGGER BOX)Border - A border that goes around the padding and content
(BIGGEST BOX)Margin - Clears an area outside the border. The margin is transparent

The total width of an element should be calculated like this:

Total element width = width + left padding + right padding + left border + right border + left margin + right margin

The total height of an element should be calculated like this:

Total element height = height + top padding + bottom padding + top border + bottom border + top margin + bottom margin